Logistic regression: Linking hypothesis and number of response options modulate inferred scalar implicature rate

Analysis of data from Jasbi, Waldon, and Degen (under review).

See the manuscript for description of the variables and experimental conditions.

The following commands run a Bayesian mixed-effects logistic regression model, perform several sanity checks and visualize the posterior probabilities over the model parameters.

# The analysis takes time to run. To reproduce please run the commented lines. We have saved the results we obtained as a dataframe.

library(brms)

# Run Bayesian mixed-effect logistic regression model

# Uncomment this line to actually run it -- but be aware that this model takes several hours to run!
#
